<P STYLE="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 1px; color: White">1 Forward - Looking Statements Important note regarding forward - looking statements: Statements made in this presentation which are not purely historical are forward - looking statements, as defined in the  Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. This includes any statements regarding management&#8217;s plans,  objectives, or goals for future operations, products or services, and forecasts of its revenues, earnings, or other  measures of performance. Such forward - looking statements may be identified by the use of words such as &#8220;believe,&#8221;  &#8220;expect,&#8221; &#8220;anticipate,&#8221; &#8220;plan,&#8221; &#8220;estimate,&#8221; &#8220;should,&#8221; &#8220;will,&#8221; &#8220;intend,&#8221; "target,&#8220; &#8220;outlook,&#8221; &#8220;project,&#8221; &#8220;guidance,&#8221; or simila r  expressions. Forward - looking statements are based on current management expectations and, by their nature, are  subject to risks and uncertainties. Actual results may differ materially from those contained in the forward - looking  statements. Factors which may cause actual results to differ materially from those contained in such forward - looking  statements include those identified in the Company&#8217;s most recent Form 10 - K and subsequent Form 10 - Qs and other  SEC filings, and such factors are incorporated herein by reference.  Trademarks: All trademarks, service marks, and trade names referenced in this material are official trademarks and the property of  their respective owners.  Presentation: Within the charts and tables presented, certain segments, columns and rows may not sum to totals shown due to  rounding. Non - GAAP Measures: This presentation includes certain non - GAAP financial measures. These non - GAAP measures are provided in addition  to, and not as substitutes for, measures of our financial performance determined in accordance with GAAP. Our  calculation of these non - GAAP measures may not be comparable to similarly titled measures of other companies due to  potential differences between companies in the method of calculation. As a result, the use of these non - GAAP measures  has limitations and should not be considered superior to, in isolation from, or as a substitute for, related GAAP measures.  Reconciliations of these non - GAAP financial measures to the most directly comparable GAAP financial measures can be  found at the end of this presentation.</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 1px; color: White">4 Our Strong Foundation We&#8217;ve strengthened our company over time by mitigating risk and prioritizing the customer experience Strengthened Credit Risk  Profile Enhanced Liquidity &amp; Interest  Rate Risk Management Sharpened Customer  Experience Focus  &#9642; Replaced high - risk  portfolios with  lower - risk  assets &#9642; Prime/super prime  consumer portfolios &#9642; Geographically anchored in  stable Midwest markets &#9642; Diversified CRE portfolio  with  limited urban office  exposure &#9642; Adopted  annual capital  stress testing  and   concentration  management controls &#9642; Achieved  100% secured  funding ratio 1 &#9642; Increased FHLB capacity &#9642; Recruited talent  for  liquidity stress testing and  A/L management roles &#9642; Added target metrics  for  repricing gap and asset  sensitivity &#9642; Implemented  balance  sheet hedging strategy &#9642; 90% top - box satisfaction  with the branch channel 2 &#9642; 3 - year high  in top - box  satisfaction with the digital  channel 2 &#9642; Relationship - focused  growth  in mass affluent,  wealth and commercial  businesses &#9642; Net customer growth  forecasted in both  consumer and business 1  Reflects total funding available within one business day. <P STYLE="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 1px; color: White">7 Our People - Led, Digitally Enabled Strategic Plan Launched in Sept. 2021, our strategic plan was designed to attract &amp; deepen relationships, enhance profitability &#9642; RM Growth &#9642; Asset - Based Lending &#9642; Equipment Finance &#9642; Auto Finance &#9642; Full Relationship Commercial &#9642; Mass Affluent &#9642; Product Enhancements &#9642; Digital Sales &#9642; New Online/Mobile Platform &#9642; Account Opening Upgrade &#9642; AI - Driven Tools &#9642; Front Line Support Enhanced our   Lending Capabilities Expanded our  Deposit Capabilities Invested in Digital  Transformation Loan Growth  Outperformance vs.  Industry Core Customer  Deposit Growth  Outperformance vs.  Industry 3 - Year High in  Digital Banking  Customer  Satisfaction 1 1 Based on quarterly top box customer satisfaction scores from internal transactional surveys. <P STYLE="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0; font-size: 1px; color: White">21 A balance sheet repositioning enhances our ability to drive improved liquidity &amp; profitability &#9642; We are currently overweight in low - margin  and low - risk assets  &#9642; The primary asset class that contributes to  this is Residential Mortgage with ~$8.8B  in assets Assets &#9642; Long standing reliance on wholesale  deposit funding has been exacerbated by  recent market conditions &#9642; To fund our organic growth plan, we plan  to outperform the market in deposit growth &#9642; In addition to our core deposit initiatives,  this transaction enables us to manage  wholesale funding within our desired  target operating levels Liabilities To address these challenges and support our organic plan, we  have announced a transaction that increases our wholesale  funding capacity Repositioning our Balance Sheet 3</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 14pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B>Associated Bank executing next phase
of strategic plan</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 1pt 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B>GREEN BAY, Wis. </B>&#8211;
November 9, 2023 &#8211; Associated Banc-Corp (NYSE: ASB) today announced plans for the next phase of the Company&rsquo;s people-led,
digitally enabled strategic plan. These plans include a series of investments in people, products and technology intended to grow and
remix the loan portfolio, accelerate core customer deposit growth, and deliver a better banking experience for customers.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&ldquo;Since launching the first phase
of our strategic plan in 2021, we&rsquo;ve steadily executed on our plans to drive high-quality loan growth, expand our deposit capabilities
and transform the digital experience for our customers,&rdquo; said President and CEO Andy Harmening. &ldquo;These efforts have resulted
in strong balance sheet expansion, and better positioned us to attract, deepen and retain customer relationships. While we continue to
benefit from these initial efforts, we also plan to capitalize on our momentum through the next phase of our strategic plan. Already
underway, this plan accelerates our efforts to attract and deepen relationships, enhance our return profile and drive improved shareholder
returns over time. We look forward to sharing updates on our progress in 2024 and beyond.&rdquo;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B>Bolstering Talent to Foster Relationships
and Balance Sheet Growth</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0.25in 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Associated today announced
further investments in talent to sharpen the Company&rsquo;s focus on relationships and drive incremental loan and deposit growth.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT>&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="padding-right: 28pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">The
                                            Company is expanding its <B>commercial middle market</B> team with plans to hire over 20
                                            additional relationship managers in focus markets such as Milwaukee, Madison, Chicago, Twin
                                            Cities and St. Louis.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 4pt 0pt 0.75in; text-indent: -0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">o&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <B>Neil
Riegelman </B>joined Associated in October as SVP, commercial banking segment leader. Riegelman brings more than 20 years of
experience to Associated Bank. Having served in progressive commercial banking roles with BMO Harris Bank since 2005, he most
recently held the position of managing director and team lead for commercial banking in Wisconsin. In his new role, Riegelman will
oversee relationship development strategies in Milwaukee and Madison.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in; text-align: left"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">o</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Associated&rsquo;s <B>Gus Hernandez
</B>has been appointed to the role of SVP, director of business banking. In his new role, he is responsible for business banking sales,
product management and credit functions across the Company&rsquo;s major metropolitan markets, including Milwaukee, Madison, Chicago
and the Twin Cities. With approximately 35 years of banking experience, Hernandez is well-positioned to bridge Associated&rsquo;s retail,
small business and commercial middle market strategies. He is also expected to lead the Company&rsquo;s efforts to add business bankers
across the footprint.</FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">o</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-right: 3pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">A
                                            new <B>commercial banking group leader</B> reporting to head of corporate banking John Utz
                                            is also expected to be announced by December 1, 2023.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Associated
                                            has also advanced its <B>private wealth</B> strategy by hiring <B>Jayne Hladio</B> as EVP,
                                            president of private wealth in October. A Midwest banking leader, Hladio brings more than
                                            30 years of market expertise to Associated. After serving a 12-year career at U.S. Bank,
                                            ultimately leading as national wealth management executive across 26 states, she most recently
                                            served as President of Midland Wealth Management and Midland Trust Co. Hladio will play an
                                            influential role in advancing the Company&rsquo;s private wealth and mass affluent strategies.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="padding-right: 5pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">As
                                            the Company looks to broaden and grow its loan portfolio, Associated also announced several
                                            adjustments to the Company&rsquo;s <B>consumer lending</B> strategy. These adjustments are
                                            expected to decrease reliance on low-yielding portfolio mortgage loans and maintain capacity
                                            for more profitable growth in other areas. Key strategic changes include:</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">o</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Limiting
                                            construction lending to customers with Associated Bank deposit relationships</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in; text-align: left"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">o</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Reducing portfolio lending to
private wealth, mass affluent and CRA customers only</FONT></TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.5in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">o</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Emphasizing
                                            the sale of conforming mortgage loans to continue fully serving our communities while maintaining
                                            capacity for more profitable loan growth in other areas</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B>Leveraging Talent, Products and Services
to Drive Core Customer Deposit Growth</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Following the successful launch of several
deposit gathering initiatives over the past 24 months, the Company is focused on accelerating core customer deposit relationships to
decrease reliance on higher-cost network and brokered funding sources. In addition to bolstering talent in key business units, the Company
is leveraging customer feedback to deliver targeted product and service enhancements and supporting these efforts with customer acquisition-focused
marketing and branding.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-right: 9pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">The
                                            planned 20+ new commercial relationship managers will be focused on attracting and deepening
                                            whole customer relationships including loans, deposits, treasury management and other services.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0"></P>

                                            drive growth in consumer and small business households, Associated plans to release several
                                            key product enhancements including early pay, automated savings and credit score monitoring.
                                            These enhancements will be supported by the Company&rsquo;s customer acquisition-focused
                                            brand strategy.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B>Continued Execution on Associated&rsquo;s
Digital Roadmap</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 9pt 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Following the successful launch
of a new digital banking platform in September of 2022, Associated has leveraged agile delivery to execute 11 major customer-facing upgrades.
This work has contributed to double-digit percentage increases in customer acquisition, double-digit percentage decreases in customer
attrition, and multi-year highs in digital banking customer satisfaction. To build on this momentum, the Company has continued to make
digital-forward investments and expects to deliver a quarterly cadence of feature and functionality upgrades. In 2024, planned initiatives
include:</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

                                            A.I. enabled chatbot,</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">

                                            enhanced digital banking experience for private wealth clients</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B>Funding Investments with Diligent
Expense Control</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">In keeping with the Company&rsquo;s
strategy, a cross-functional team has reviewed Associated&rsquo;s expense structure in partnership with a third-party consultant to identify
cost saves and reinvest into the Company&rsquo;s growth initiatives. Through these efforts, the Company has identified $25 million to
$30 million in noninterest expense reductions for 2024. Expense reductions are primarily comprised of FTE reductions, branch consolidations
and decreased discretionary spending. In connection with these expense reduction initiatives, the Company expects to incur a one-time
charge of approximately $5 million in severance and other expenses in the fourth quarter of 2023.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">After fully implementing these expense
reductions and reinvestments, Associated&rsquo;s noninterest expense is expected to grow by between 3% and 4% in both 2023 and 2024,
excluding the one-time expenses anticipated in the fourth quarter of 2023.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><P STYLE="margin: 0pt">&nbsp;</P></DIV>

    <!-- Field: /Page -->

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B>Balance Sheet Repositioning</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 1pt 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">To accelerate the financial
impacts of the Associated&rsquo;s organic growth strategy, the Company also announced today a balance sheet repositioning transaction.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="padding-right: 17pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Under
                                            the terms of the transaction, Associated Bank has sold approximately $0.8 billion of investment
                                            securities and has agreed to sell approximately $1 billion in mortgage loans, generally in
                                            single-product relationships. The sale of the mortgage loans is expected to close by year-end
                                            2023.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top">
<TD STYLE="width: 0"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.25in"><FONT STYLE="font-family: Symbol">&middot;</FONT></TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify; padding-right: 2pt"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">The
                                            transaction is expected to result in an after-tax loss of approximately $157 million which
                                            will cause the Company to report a net loss for the fourth quarter of 2023.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">The transaction is expected to
significantly increase Associated&rsquo;s wholesale funding capacity by paying down FHLB advances and other high-cost funding, while
also removing low-yielding assets from the books. The Company has also chosen to reinvest over $700 million into investment
securities at current rates and cash.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 1pt 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Associated Bank management intends
to provide additional details on its strategic plan and initiatives in a conference call for investors and analysts at 5:00 p.m. Central
Time (CT) today, November 9, 2023. Interested parties can access the live webcast of the call through the Investor Relations section
of the Company&rsquo;s website, http://investor.associatedbank.com. Parties may also dial into the call at 877-407-8037 (domestic) or 201-689-8037
(international) and request the Associated Banc-Corp strategic update call. An accompanying slide presentation will be available on the
Company&rsquo;s website just prior to the call. An audio archive of the webcast will be available on the Company&rsquo;s website approximately fifteen
minutes after the call is over.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 1pt 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">An investor presentation has
been filed as a Form 8-K with the Securities and Exchange Commission and can be accessed via Associated Banc-Corp&rsquo;s website at
<U>http://investor.associatedbank.com</U>.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt"><B>ABOUT ASSOCIATED BANC-CORP</B></FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">&nbsp;</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"><FONT STYLE="font-size: 10pt">Associated Banc-Corp (NYSE: ASB) has
total assets of $42 billion and is the largest bank holding company based in Wisconsin. Headquartered in Green Bay, Wisconsin, Associated
is a leading Midwest banking franchise, offering a full range of financial products and services from more than 200 banking locations
serving more than 100 communities throughout Wisconsin, Illinois and Minnesota. The Company also operates loan production offices in
Indiana, Michigan, Missouri, New York, Ohio and Texas. Associated Bank, N.A. is an Equal Housing Lender, Equal Opportunity Lender and
Member FDIC. More information about Associated Banc-Corp is available at www.associatedbank.com.</FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0pt 0"></P>

and forecasts of its revenues, earnings, or other measures of performance. Such forward-looking statements may be identified by the
use of words such as &ldquo;believe,&rdquo; &ldquo;expect,&rdquo; &ldquo;anticipate,&rdquo; &ldquo;plan,&rdquo;

var Show={};Show.LastAR=null,Show.showAR=function(a,r,w){if(Show.LastAR)Show.hideAR();var e=a;while(e&&e.nodeName!='TABLE')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e||e.nodeName!='TABLE'){var ref=((window)?w.document:document).getElementById(r);if(ref){e=ref.cloneNode(!0);
e.removeAttribute('id');a.parentNode.appendChild(e)}}
if(e)e.style.display='block';Show.LastAR=e};Show.hideAR=function(){Show.LastAR.style.display='none'};Show.toggleNext=function(a){var e=a;while(e.nodeName!='DIV')e=e.nextSibling;if(!e.style){}else if(!e.style.display){}else{var d,p_;if(e.style.display=='none'){d='block';p='-'}else{d='none';p='+'}
e.style.display=d;if(a.textContent){a.textContent=p+a.textContent.substring(1)}else{a.innerText=p+a.innerText.substring(1)}}}
